  <tr>
   <td colspan="4" class="content">
    <pre>The bug has an attachment, guide.png, which shows a few oddities on the 
left navigation and elsewhere. Specifically:

* The orange bar at the top of the "Represent your project" text is wider 
than seems appropriate, it seems to me.

* The navigation boxes such as "Use proven social strategies" have no 
bottom bar, which is not consistent with the rest of the site.

* The main content area is in a gray box with an outline, which is inside 
a white box with a dashed outline, which is within a gray-ish background 
rectangle, which is within the usual hatched background. This one in 
particular irks me; it's a lot of unusual layout for no clear reason.

I hope that helps explain the general problem that we see! (I say "we" 
because Elana and I both noticed this and decided to file the bug 
together.)

As for a prospective solution, I think Elana's and my idea was that if we 
make this page/set of pages use the same CSS+HTML structure as some other 
page(s), then we can avoid maintaining something special to this page, on 
the theory that doing something different here means we'll have to make 
sure it stays good-looking throughout time, and we're concerned that 
having a special-case layout for these pages isn't something we've been 
able to reliably maintain.

Naturally, Elana, if I mis-stated something, feel free to say "Asheesh is 
speaking for himself."

I hope that explains the reason we suggested this solution strategy! As 
always, more discussion/feedback/ideas welcome.</pre>
   </td>
  </tr>
 
 
